/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `authClockSkewSeconds` config field (reads `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS` env, default 60)\n   177→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired auth middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n   178→- `services/backend/package.json` — Added `tweetnacl` (^1.0.3) and `bs58` (^6.0.0) dependencies\n   179→\n   180→Verification:\n   181→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   182→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   183→- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n   184→- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass\n   185→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   186→\n   187→## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-11T14:36:48Z — OK\n   188→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   189→\n   190→## Iteration 8 — Rate limiting middleware\n   191→\n   192→**Item**: [backend] Rate limiting middleware (`src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`)\n   193→**Status**: Done\n   194→\n   195→Created:\n   196→- `services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` — In-memory sliding-window rate limiter\n   197→  - `createRateLimitMiddleware(config)` factory returns Hono middleware\n   198→  - Skips non-POST requests (GET endpoints not rate-limited)\n   199→  - Per-wallet limit keyed by `wallet` field from JSON body (default 10/min via `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET`)\n   200→  - Global limit for all POST requests combined (default 100/min via `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL`)\n   201→  - Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when either limit exceeded\n   202→  - Sliding window: prunes expired timestamps on each check\n   203→  - Counters reset on service restart (in-memory, no Redis)\n   204→\n   205→Updated:\n   206→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `rateLimitPerWallet` and `rateLimitGlobal` config fields\n   207→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired rate limit middleware on `/fairness/*` routes (before auth middleware)\n   208→\n   209→Verification:\n   210→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   211→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   212→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   213→- `pnpm typecheck` — passes\n   214→- `pnpm lint` — passes\n   215→\n   216→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:42:00Z — OK\n   217→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   218→\n   219→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:38:45Z — OK\n   220→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   221→\n   222→## Iteration 9 — Settlement worker poll loop\n   223→\n   224→**Item**: [backend] Settlement worker poll loop (`src/worker/settlement.ts`)\n   225→**Status**: Done\n   226→\n   227→Created:\n   228→- `services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` — Settlement worker that polls chain for locked matches\n   229→  - `createSettlementWorker(deps)` factory returns a `SettlementWorker` with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, `poll()`\n   230→  - Polls via `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters: dataSize=246, phase byte at offset 114 = PHASE_LOCKED (1), server pubkey at offset 72 matches service keypair\n   231→  - Parses target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148) from account data\n   232→  - Tracks discovered PDAs in-memory to log `match_detected` only once per match\n   233→  - Transitions DB phase from `created` → `locked` when match first detected on-chain\n   234→  - Calls optional `onSettleReady` callback when target_slot is reached (hook for settle-tx module)\n   235→  - Configurable poll interval (default 2s via `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` env var)\n   236→  - Error-resilient: logs errors but doesn't crash the loop\n   237→\n   238→Updated:\n   239→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `workerPollIntervalMs` config field (reads `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS`, default 2000)\n   240→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Imports and starts settlement worker on service boot\n   241→\n   242→Verification:\n   243→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   244→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   245→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   246→\n   247→## Iteration 9 — 2026-03-11T14:46:02Z — OK\n   248→- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n   249→\n   250→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af244c03-5c35-4a31-9aaa-3171645fdb08","uuid":"11057a7f-bbb5-4644-b651-f4e68e78dd26","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/006-fairness-backend/history.md","content":"# Implementation History — 006-fairness-backend\n\nIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\nattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\nof every iteration to understand prior context.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 — Scaffold `services/backend/` package\n\n**Item**: [infra] Scaffold `services/backend/` package\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/package.json` — `@rng-utopia/backend`, Hono + `@solana/web3.js` deps, ESM, tsx watch dev script\n- `services/backend/tsconfig.json` — extends `@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.node.json`, overrides rootDir/outDir\n- `services/backend/eslint.config.js` — uses shared `nodeConfig`\n- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — env config loader reading `DATABASE_URL`, `RPC_URL`, `SERVER_KEYPAIR` (JSON array keypair), `PORT` (default 3100)\n- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Hono HTTP server with placeholder `/health` endpoint, uses Hono's `export default { port, fetch }` pattern\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm install` — success (hono resolved as +1 new package)\n- `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/backend build` — success (tsc --noEmit, clean)\n- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass (0 errors, existing warnings only)\n- `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/platform build` — success (no regression)\n\nNote: `pnpm build:all` has pre-existing failures in `chart-the-course`, `coinflip`, `slots-utopia`, `tug-of-earn` apps — unrelated to this change.\n\n## Iteration 1 — 2026-03-11T14:00:43Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n\n## Iteration 2 — Postgres migrations\n\n**Item**: [backend] Postgres migrations\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql` — `rounds` + `operator_events` tables with all columns, types, constraints, and 4 indexes (`rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`)\n- `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — Simple migration runner with `_migrations` version tracking table, idempotent (re-run skips applied), CLI with `status` subcommand\n- Added `postgres` dependency (postgresjs v3) to `services/backend/package.json`\n- Added `migrate` and `migrate:status` scripts to package.json\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n- `pnpm lint` — backend passes (0 errors)\n- `pnpm migrate` — applied 001_init.sql successfully against local Postgres\n- Re-ran `pnpm migrate` — idempotent (\"All migrations are up to date\")\n- Verified all tables, columns, and indexes via `psql \\d` output\n\n## Iteration 2 — 2026-03-11T14:08:25Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n\n## Iteration 3 — DB client module\n\n**Item**: [backend] DB client module (`src/db.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client module with typed query functions using `postgres` (postgresjs) library\n\nFeatures:\n- `createDb(databaseUrl)` factory returns a `Db` interface with connection pool\n- `insertRound(params)` — inserts a new round (throws on duplicate PDA via primary key)\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` — transitions phase with unidirectional guard. Validates against `VALID_TRANSITIONS` state machine: `created→locked`, `created→expired`, `locked→settling`, `settling→settled`. Sets `updated_at = now()` on every phase change. Optional extra column updates (target_slot, settle_tx, result fields) via COALESCE.\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)` — returns single round or undefined\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` — returns all rounds matching a phase\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload?)` — appends to operator_events audit log\n- `close()` — gracefully ends connection pool\n- TypeScript types: `RoundPhase`, `OperatorEventType`, `Round`, `InsertRoundParams`, `OperatorEvent`, `Db`\n- `secret` column is never logged (no console.log or error message references)\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm typecheck` — passes (0 errors)\n- `pnpm lint` — passes (0 errors)\n\n## Iteration 3 — 2026-03-11T14:13:45Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n## Iteration 4 — Secret generation + commitment utilities\n\n**Item**: [backend] Secret generation + commitment utilities (`src/fairness.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/fairness.ts` — Three exported functions:\n  - `generateSecret()`: 32-byte CSPRNG via `crypto.randomBytes(32)`\n  - `computeCommitment(secret)`: SHA256 hash matching `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` algorithm\n  - `deriveMatchPda(creator, nonce)`: PDA derivation with seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]` using coinflip program ID\n- `services/backend/src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` — 11 unit tests covering:\n  - Secret: 32-byte length, uniqueness\n  - Commitment: known SHA256 constant match, algorithm cross-check, determinism, different-input-different-output\n  - PDA: return type, manual derivation match, bigint nonce support, different nonces/creators produce different PDAs\n- `services/backend/vitest.config.ts` — vitest config (node environment)\n\nVerification:\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `npx eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `npx vitest run` — 11 tests pass\n\n## Iteration 4 — 2026-03-11T14:18:52Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n\n## Iteration 5 — Partial transaction builder\n\n**Item**: [backend] Partial transaction builder (`src/tx-builder.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` — Builds `create_match` transactions without `@coral-xyz/anchor` dependency\n\nFeatures:\n- `buildCreateMatchTx(params)` — async function that:\n  - Derives match PDA via `deriveMatchPda(creator, nonce)` from fairness.ts\n  - Derives config PDA with seeds `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n  - Manually encodes Borsh instruction data: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + tier(1) + side(1) + nonce(8) = 50 bytes\n  - Assembles `TransactionInstruction` with accounts in IDL order: creator (signer+writable), server (signer), coinflip_match (writable), config, system_program\n  - Sets creator wallet as fee payer (server pays zero on-chain cost)\n  - Fetches recent blockhash at build time via `connection.getLatestBlockhash()`\n  - Partially signs with server keypair only\n  - Serializes with `requireAllSignatures: false` and returns base64 string + matchPda\n- Exported `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` from fairness.ts (was module-private, needed by tx-builder)\n- Uses only `@solana/web3.js` (no new dependencies)\n\nVerification:\n- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests still pass\n\n## Iteration 5 — 2026-03-11T14:24:21Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n\n## Iteration 6 — POST /fairness/coinflip/create endpoint\n\n**Item**: [backend] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` endpoint handler\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` — Hono route handler with `createCoinflipRoutes(deps)` factory\n  - Validates request body: wallet (base58), tier (0-255), side (0|1), nonce (non-negative int), timestamp, signature\n  - Generates 32-byte secret via `generateSecret()`, computes SHA256 commitment\n  - Derives match PDA, checks DB for duplicate (409 Conflict)\n  - Builds + partial-signs `create_match` tx via `buildCreateMatchTx()`\n  - Stores round in DB (phase: `created`), writes `secret_generated` operator event\n  - Returns `{transaction, matchPda, commitment}` (200)\n  - Race condition handling: duplicate PDA insert caught at DB level as well as pre-check\n\nUpdated:\n- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — initializes DB connection pool + Solana Connection, wires `createCoinflipRoutes` at `/fairness/coinflip`\n\nVerification:\n- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass\n\n## Iteration 6 — 2026-03-11T14:29:16Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n\n## Iteration 7 — Request authentication middleware\n\n**Item**: [backend] Request authentication middleware (`src/middleware/auth.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/middleware/auth.ts` — Hono middleware for Ed25519 wallet signature verification\n  - Skips non-POST requests (GET endpoints unauthenticated per spec)\n  - Verifies Ed25519 signature over canonical payload `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})`\n  - Uses `tweetnacl` for signature verification, `bs58` for base58 decoding\n  - Rejects expired timestamps (configurable clock skew, default 60s)\n  - Returns 401 for invalid/missing/expired signatures\n  - Validates signature length (64 bytes) and pubkey length (32 bytes)\n\nUpdated:\n- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `authClockSkewSeconds` config field (reads `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS` env, default 60)\n- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired auth middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n- `services/backend/package.json` — Added `tweetnacl` (^1.0.3) and `bs58` (^6.0.0) dependencies\n\nVerification:\n- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass\n- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n\n## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-11T14:36:48Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n\n## Iteration 8 — Rate limiting middleware\n\n**Item**: [backend] Rate limiting middleware (`src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` — In-memory sliding-window rate limiter\n  - `createRateLimitMiddleware(config)` factory returns Hono middleware\n  - Skips non-POST requests (GET endpoints not rate-limited)\n  - Per-wallet limit keyed by `wallet` field from JSON body (default 10/min via `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET`)\n  - Global limit for all POST requests combined (default 100/min via `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL`)\n  - Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when either limit exceeded\n  - Sliding window: prunes expired timestamps on each check\n  - Counters reset on service restart (in-memory, no Redis)\n\nUpdated:\n- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `rateLimitPerWallet` and `rateLimitGlobal` config fields\n- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired rate limit middleware on `/fairness/*` routes (before auth middleware)\n\nVerification:\n- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n- `pnpm typecheck` — passes\n- `pnpm lint` — passes\n\n## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:42:00Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n\n## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:38:45Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n\n## Iteration 9 — Settlement worker poll loop\n\n**Item**: [backend] Settlement worker poll loop (`src/worker/settlement.ts`)\n**Status**: Done\n\nCreated:\n- `services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` — Settlement worker that polls chain for locked matches\n  - `createSettlementWorker(deps)` factory returns a `SettlementWorker` with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, `poll()`\n  - Polls via `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters: dataSize=246, phase byte at offset 114 = PHASE_LOCKED (1), server pubkey at offset 72 matches service keypair\n  - Parses target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148) from account data\n  - Tracks discovered PDAs in-memory to log `match_detected` only once per match\n  - Transitions DB phase from `created` → `locked` when match first detected on-chain\n  - Calls optional `onSettleReady` callback when target_slot is reached (hook for settle-tx module)\n  - Configurable poll interval (default 2s via `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` env var)\n  - Error-resilient: logs errors but doesn't crash the loop\n\nUpdated:\n- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `workerPollIntervalMs` config field (reads `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS`, default 2000)\n- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Imports and starts settlement worker on service boot\n\nVerification:\n- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n\n## Iteration 9 — 2026-03-11T14:46:02Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n\n","numLines":250,"startLine":1,"totalLines":250}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P7ZkTksMaKajPhPV6C89Xe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: [006] Fairness Backend — Coinflip MVP\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P0 |\n     9→| Phase | 1 |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 9 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→Off-chain service that holds server secrets and orchestrates the commit-reveal fairness\n    17→model defined in Spec 005 (Hybrid Fairness). Today the frontend generates secrets\n    18→client-side (dev-mode) — this service moves secret generation to the server, co-signs\n    19→match creation transactions, watches for locked matches, and settles them by revealing\n    20→the secret on-chain.\n    21→\n    22→Scoped to **coinflip only**. Crash, Lord of RNGs, and other games are explicitly deferred\n    23→until the coinflip backend is proven stable.\n    24→\n    25→## User Stories\n    26→\n    27→- As a player, I want the server to generate and guard the secret so that neither I nor\n    28→  the server alone can predict the outcome.\n    29→- As a player, I want to create a match with a single wallet approval so that the\n    30→  experience feels instant despite server co-signing.\n    31→- As a player, I want my match settled automatically after my opponent joins so that I\n    32→  don't have to take any action to see the result.\n    33→- As an operator, I want locked matches settled within seconds of entropy availability\n    34→  so that players never wait unnecessarily.\n    35→- As a verifier, I want a public endpoint that serves the secret (post-settlement) and\n    36→  all inputs to the result formula so that I can independently confirm fairness.\n    37→\n    38→---\n    39→\n    40→## Scope Alignment\n    41→\n    42→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Coinflip (Phase 1), Backend Services\n    43→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    44→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 — required before coinflip can leave dev-mode fairness\n    45→\n    46→## Required Context Files\n    47→\n    48→- `docs/specs/005-hybrid-fairness/spec.md` — On-chain commit-reveal + slot hash model\n    49→- `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` — Architecture patterns, testing strategy\n    50→- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — VRF provider decision, fee structure\n    51→- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/create_match.rs` — Account layout, signer requirements\n    52→- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/settle.rs` — Permissionless settlement, account layout, event shape\n    53→- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` — `CoinflipMatch` fields, phases, `MatchSettled` event\n    54→- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fairness.rs` — `verify_commitment()`, `derive_result()`, `ALGORITHM_VERSION`\n    55→- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fees.rs` — 300 bps total, `calculate_net_payout()`\n    56→\n    57→## Contract Files\n    58→\n    59→- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` — `computeCommitment()`, `verifyCommitment()` (reuse in backend)\n    60→- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` — Typed IDL for tx building\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→## Core Design\n    65→\n    66→### Architecture\n    67→\n    68→Single Node.js/TypeScript process using **Hono** (lightweight HTTP framework) with three\n    69→internal modules:\n    70→\n    71→```\n    72→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    73→│                 Fairness Service             │\n    74→│                                             │\n    75→│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐ │\n    76→│  │ Signing  │  │Settlement│  │  Rounds   │ │\n    77→│  │ Module   │  │ Worker   │  │  Module   │ │\n    78→│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └─────┬─────┘ │\n    79→│       │              │              │       │\n    80→│       └──────────┬───┘──────────────┘       │\n    81→│                  │                          │\n    82→│           ┌──────┴──────┐                   │\n    83→│           │  Postgres   │                   │\n    84→│           │  (rounds +  │                   │\n    85→│           │   events)   │                   │\n    86→│           └─────────────┘                   │\n    87→└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→**Signing Module** — Handles `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`. Generates secret,\n    91→computes commitment, builds the `create_match` transaction using the coinflip IDL,\n    92→partially signs with the server keypair, returns the serialized transaction to the caller.\n    93→\n    94→**Settlement Worker** — Polls for matches in PHASE_LOCKED where `target_slot` has been\n    95→reached. Reads entropy, builds and submits the `settle` transaction with the stored secret.\n    96→Retries on transient failures; logs to `operator_events`.\n    97→\n    98→**Rounds Module** — Handles `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`. Serves round lifecycle data\n    99→and verification payloads. Reads from DB, redacts secret for unsettled rounds.\n   100→\n   101→### Signer Model\n   102→\n   103→One server keypair for MVP, loaded from environment (`SERVER_KEYPAIR`). This keypair:\n   104→- Co-signs `create_match` transactions (appears as `server: Signer` in the instruction)\n   105→- Pays the settlement transaction fee (~0.000005 SOL per settle)\n   106→- Does NOT need to be the same key that calls `settle` (settle is permissionless — anyone\n   107→  with the secret can call it), but using the server key simplifies operational monitoring\n   108→\n   109→Future: split into separate signing authority (cold, for create) and settlement authority\n   110→(hot, for settle). The on-chain program already supports this — `settle` has no server\n   111→signer constraint.\n   112→\n   113→### Transaction Flow\n   114→\n   115→```\n   116→Player                    Backend                     Chain\n   117→  │                          │                          │\n   118→  ├─ POST /create ──────────►│                          │\n   119→  │  {tier, side, wallet}    │                          │\n   120→  │                          │─ generate secret         │\n   121→  │                          │─ commitment = sha256()   │\n   122→  │                          │─ build create_match tx   │\n   123→  │                          │─ server partial-sign     │\n   124→  │                          │─ store secret in DB      │\n   125→  │◄─ {tx, matchPda} ───────│                          │\n   126→  │                          │                          │\n   127→  ├─ co-sign + submit ─────────────────────────────────►│\n   128→  │                          │                          │─ create match PDA\n   129→  │                          │                          │\n   130→  │         ... opponent joins (user-submitted) ...     │\n   131→  │                          │                          │─ PHASE_LOCKED, target_slot set\n   132→  │                          │                          │\n   133→  │                          │◄── poll / subscription ──│\n   134→  │                          │─ wait for target_slot    │\n   135→  │                          │─ build settle tx         │\n   136→  │                          │─ submit settle ─────────►│\n   137→  │                          │                          │─ verify commitment\n   138→  │                          │                          │─ derive result\n   139→  │                          │                          │─ pay winner\n   140→  │                          │                          │─ emit MatchSettled\n   141→  │                          │                          │\n   142→  │                          │─ update DB (settled)     │\n   143→```\n   144→\n   145→### Database Schema\n   146→\n   147→Two tables — `rounds` for state, `operator_events` for append-only audit trail.\n   148→\n   149→#### `rounds`\n   150→\n   151→| Column | Type | Notes |\n   152→|--------|------|-------|\n   153→| `pda` | `TEXT PRIMARY KEY` | Base58 match PDA address |\n   154→| `game` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `'coinflip'` (extensible later) |\n   155→| `creator` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 creator wallet |\n   156→| `server_key` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 server pubkey used |\n   157→| `secret` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | 32-byte server secret |\n   158→| `commitment` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | SHA256(secret) |\n   159→| `tier` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Tier index |\n   160→| `side` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Creator's chosen side |\n   161→| `nonce` | `BIGINT NOT NULL` | Match nonce |\n   162→| `phase` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `created`, `locked`, `settling`, `settled`, `expired` |\n   163→| `target_slot` | `BIGINT` | Set when match transitions to locked |\n   164→| `settle_tx` | `TEXT` | Settlement tx signature |\n   165→| `settle_attempts` | `INT DEFAULT 0` | Retry counter |\n   166→| `result_hash` | `BYTEA` | 32-byte result (post-settlement) |\n   167→| `result_side` | `SMALLINT` | 0=Heads, 1=Tails (post-settlement) |\n   168→| `winner` | `TEXT` | Base58 winner address (post-settlement) |\n   169→| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   170→| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   171→\n   172→#### `operator_events`\n   173→\n   174→| Column | Type | Notes |\n   175→|--------|------|-------|\n   176→| `id` | `BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY` | Auto-increment |\n   177→| `pda` | `TEXT` | Nullable — some events are system-level |\n   178→| `event_type` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `secret_generated`, `tx_built`, `match_detected`, `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, `settle_retried`, `timeout_detected` |\n   179→| `payload` | `JSONB` | Event-specific data |\n   180→| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   181→\n   182→**Indexes**: `rounds(phase)` for settlement worker queries, `rounds(creator)` for lookup,\n   183→`operator_events(pda, created_at)` for round history, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)` for monitoring.\n   184→\n   185→---\n   186→\n   187→## Functional Requirements\n   188→\n   189→<!-- FR acceptance criteria checkboxes are audited by /gap-analysis after completion.\n   190→     Each checkbox gets an HTML comment annotation: satisfied/deferred/gap with evidence. -->\n   191→\n   192→### FR-1: Secret Generation & Transaction Signing\n   193→\n   194→The service generates a cryptographically secure secret, computes the commitment,\n   195→builds a `create_match` transaction with the server's partial signature, and returns it\n   196→to the requesting wallet for co-signing and submission.\n   197→\n   198→**Endpoint**: `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`\n   199→\n   200→**Request body**:\n   201→```json\n   202→{\n   203→  \"wallet\": \"<base58 creator pubkey>\",\n   204→  \"tier\": 3,\n   205→  \"side\": 0,\n   206→  \"nonce\": 42,\n   207→  \"timestamp\": 1710000000,\n   208→  \"signature\": \"<base58 Ed25519 signature over canonical payload>\"\n   209→}\n   210→```\n   211→\n   212→**Response** (200):\n   213→```json\n   214→{\n   215→  \"transaction\": \"<base64 serialized partial tx>\",\n   216→  \"matchPda\": \"<base58 PDA address>\",\n   217→  \"commitment\": \"<hex commitment>\"\n   218→}\n   219→```\n   220→\n   221→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   222→- [ ] Secret is 32 bytes generated via Node.js `crypto.randomBytes(32)` (CSPRNG)\n   223→- [ ] Commitment is computed using the same algorithm as `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` (`sha256(secret)`)\n   224→- [ ] Transaction is built using the coinflip IDL (`create_match` instruction) with correct accounts and args\n   225→- [ ] Server keypair partially signs the transaction (server appears as `server: Signer`)\n   226→- [ ] User's wallet is set as fee payer — server pays zero on-chain cost for creation\n   227→- [ ] Secret is stored in the `rounds` table keyed by match PDA before the response is returned\n   228→- [ ] An `operator_events` entry of type `secret_generated` is written\n   229→- [ ] Match PDA is derived using seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]` matching the on-chain program\n   230→- [ ] If the same PDA already exists in the DB (duplicate nonce), the endpoint returns 409 Conflict\n   231→- [ ] Recent blockhash is fetched at request time (transaction expires naturally via Solana's ~60s blockhash window)\n   232→\n   233→### FR-2: Settlement Worker\n   234→\n   235→A background process that detects locked matches and submits settlement transactions\n   236→once entropy is available.\n   237→\n   238→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   239→- [ ] Worker polls the chain (via `getProgramAccounts` or equivalent) for `CoinflipMatch` accounts in `PHASE_LOCKED` where the `server` field matches the service's keypair\n   240→- [ ] For each locked match, worker checks if `target_slot` has been reached (current slot >= target_slot)\n   241→- [ ] Worker retrieves the stored secret from the `rounds` table using the match PDA\n   242→- [ ] Worker builds and submits the `settle` instruction with the secret, all required accounts (match PDA, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, profiles, platform program), and the server keypair as caller\n   243→- [ ] On successful settlement, worker updates the round's DB phase to `settled` and stores `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`\n   244→- [ ] On transient failure (tx dropped, blockhash expired, network error), worker retries up to 5 times with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s)\n   245→- [ ] On permanent failure (commitment mismatch, invalid phase, account not found), worker marks the round as failed and logs to `operator_events` without retrying\n   246→- [ ] Worker poll interval is configurable (default: 2 seconds)\n   247→- [ ] Worker logs each attempt to `operator_events` with type `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, or `settle_retried`\n   248→- [ ] If `resolve_deadline` has passed and settlement has not succeeded, worker logs a `timeout_detected` event (the on-chain timeout refund is triggered by any user, not by the backend)\n   249→\n   250→### FR-3: Round State Storage\n   251→\n   252→Postgres tables store the full lifecycle of each round with an append-only operator\n   253→event log for auditability.\n   254→\n   255→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   256→- [ ] `rounds` table schema matches the design in Core Design section (all columns, types, constraints)\n   257→- [ ] `operator_events` table schema matches the design in Core Design section\n   258→- [ ] Phase transitions follow this state machine: `created` → `locked` → `settling` → `settled`; or `created` → `expired` (if tx never lands on-chain). The worker discovers matches on-chain via polling — no intermediate states needed for phases the backend can't directly observe.\n   259→- [ ] Phase transitions are unidirectional — no backward transitions allowed at the application layer\n   260→- [ ] `secret` column is stored as raw bytes, never logged or exposed in error messages\n   261→- [ ] `updated_at` is set on every phase transition\n   262→- [ ] Database migrations are versioned and idempotent (can re-run safely)\n   263→- [ ] Indexes exist on `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, and `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n   264→\n   265→### FR-4: Round Verification Endpoint\n   266→\n   267→Public endpoint serving round lifecycle data and post-settlement verification payloads.\n   268→\n   269→**Endpoint**: `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`\n   270→\n   271→**Response** (settled round):\n   272→```json\n   273→{\n   274→  \"pda\": \"<base58>\",\n   275→  \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n   276→  \"phase\": \"settled\",\n   277→  \"commitment\": \"<hex>\",\n   278→  \"secret\": \"<hex>\",\n   279→  \"algorithmVersion\": 1,\n   280→  \"targetSlot\": 312000000,\n   281→  \"resultHash\": \"<hex>\",\n   282→  \"resultSide\": 0,\n   283→  \"winner\": \"<base58>\",\n   284→  \"settleTx\": \"<base58 tx signature>\",\n   285→  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-11T12:00:00Z\",\n   286→  \"verification\": {\n   287→    \"commitmentCheck\": \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n   288→    \"resultFormula\": \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n   289→    \"entropySource\": \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\"\n   290→  }\n   291→}\n   292→```\n   293→\n   294→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   295→- [ ] Endpoint returns round data for any known PDA\n   296→- [ ] For unsettled rounds (`phase` != `settled`), the `secret` field is omitted from the response\n   297→- [ ] For settled rounds, the response includes `secret`, `resultHash`, `resultSide`, `winner`, and `settleTx`\n   298→- [ ] Response includes a `verification` object with human-readable descriptions of the fairness checks\n   299→- [ ] Endpoint returns 404 for unknown PDAs\n   300→- [ ] Response is JSON with consistent field naming (camelCase)\n   301→- [ ] No sensitive operational data (server keypair, internal IDs) is exposed\n   302→\n   303→### FR-5: Request Authentication\n   304→\n   305→Requests to state-changing endpoints are authenticated via wallet-signed payloads\n   306→to prevent spoofing without requiring session infrastructure.\n   307→\n   308→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   309→- [ ] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` requires a valid Ed25519 signature over a canonical payload\n   310→- [ ] Canonical payload is: `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})` with keys in that exact order\n   311→- [ ] Signature is verified against the `wallet` pubkey using `@noble/ed25519` or `tweetnacl`\n   312→- [ ] Requests with a `timestamp` more than 60 seconds from server time are rejected (replay protection)\n   313→- [ ] Requests with an invalid or missing signature return 401 Unauthorized\n   314→- [ ] `GET` endpoints (rounds, health) require no authentication\n   315→- [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable (default: 60 seconds)\n   316→\n   317→### FR-6: Health & Observability\n   318→\n   319→Operational endpoints and structured logging for monitoring service health.\n   320→\n   321→**Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n   322→\n   323→**Response**:\n   324→```json\n   325→{\n   326→  \"status\": \"ok\",\n   327→  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n   328→  \"serverKey\": \"<base58 server pubkey>\",\n   329→  \"solBalance\": 1.5,\n   330→  \"dbConnected\": true,\n   331→  \"workerRunning\": true,\n   332→  \"unsettledCount\": 3,\n   333→  \"oldestUnsettledAge\": 12\n   334→}\n   335→```\n   336→\n   337→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   338→- [ ] `GET /health` returns server status including: service version, server public key, SOL balance of server keypair, DB connectivity, worker status, count of unsettled rounds, age (seconds) of oldest unsettled round\n   339→- [ ] Health endpoint requires no authentication\n   340→- [ ] All log output is structured JSON (timestamp, level, message, optional fields)\n   341→- [ ] Logs include round PDA context where applicable (settlement attempts, errors)\n   342→- [ ] No secrets or private keys appear in logs at any level\n   343→- [ ] SOL balance below a configurable threshold (default: 0.1 SOL) triggers a warning-level log on each health check\n   344→- [ ] `operator_events` table is queryable for monitoring dashboards (no dedicated endpoint required for MVP; direct DB access is acceptable)\n   345→\n   346→### FR-7: Rate Limiting\n   347→\n   348→Per-wallet and global rate limits to prevent abuse of the create endpoint.\n   349→\n   350→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   351→- [ ] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` is rate-limited per wallet (default: 10 requests per minute)\n   352→- [ ] A global rate limit caps total create requests (default: 100 requests per minute)\n   353→- [ ] Rate limiting is in-memory (no Redis dependency for MVP)\n   354→- [ ] Exceeded limits return HTTP 429 with a `Retry-After` header\n   355→- [ ] `GET` endpoints are not rate-limited for MVP\n   356→- [ ] Rate limit windows and thresholds are configurable via environment variables\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→## Success Criteria\n   361→\n   362→- Server generates secrets and co-signs create transactions — frontend no longer holds secrets\n   363→- Locked matches are settled automatically within 10 seconds of entropy availability (p95)\n   364→- Settlement retry logic handles transient RPC failures without manual intervention\n   365→- Any settled round can be independently verified via the public rounds endpoint\n   366→- Service runs as a single process with < 100 MB memory footprint under normal load\n   367→- Zero SOL cost for match creation (server is signer but user is fee payer)\n   368→\n   369→---\n   370→\n   371→## Dependencies\n   372→\n   373→- Spec 005 (Hybrid Fairness) — on-chain commit-reveal model must be implemented. **Spec 005 must set timeout to 300s** (not 120s) so that if the backend is down, players get a permissionless refund. The backend requires server co-sign for new games, so no new matches can be created during downtime anyway — timeout refund is the complete safety net.\n   374→- Coinflip program deployed with `server: Signer` on `create_match` and permissionless `settle`\n   375→- `packages/fairness/` — `computeCommitment()` and `verifyCommitment()` functions\n   376→- `packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` — Typed IDL for transaction building\n   377→- Postgres instance (local Docker for dev, managed for production)\n   378→- Solana RPC endpoint with `getProgramAccounts` support\n   379→\n   380→## Assumptions\n   381→\n   382→- The on-chain coinflip program is already deployed with the Spec 005 commit-reveal model\n   383→- A single server keypair is sufficient for MVP (no key rotation during operation)\n   384→- In-memory rate limiting is acceptable (service restarts reset counters)\n   385→- Postgres is the only external dependency (no Redis, no message queue)\n   386→- The settlement worker is the only settler — no competing settlers for MVP\n   387→- Frontend will be updated separately to call the backend instead of generating secrets client-side\n   388→\n   389→---\n   390→\n   391→## Deferred Items\n   392→\n   393→| Item | Rationale |\n   394→|------|-----------|\n   395→| Multi-game support (Crash, Lord of RNGs, Slots) | Prove the model on coinflip first; each game has different entropy capture timing |\n   396→| Key rotation / split authorities | Single keypair is fine for MVP; add when operational maturity requires it |\n   397→| WebSocket push for settlement notifications | Frontend already polls on-chain state; adding WS is a UX optimization, not a blocker |\n   398→| Redis-backed rate limiting | In-memory is sufficient until horizontal scaling is needed |\n   399→| Batch settlement (multiple matches per tx) | Premature optimization; single-match settlement is simpler to debug |\n   400→| Verification page / UI | The endpoint exists; a standalone verification UI is a frontend concern |\n   401→| Automated server keypair funding | Manual top-up for MVP; automate when tx volume justifies it |\n   402→| Horizontal scaling / multiple workers | Single process handles expected MVP load; scale when needed |\n   403→| Event-driven settlement (geyser/websocket subscription) | Polling is simpler and sufficient; switch if latency budget tightens |\n   404→| Metrics endpoint (Prometheus) | Structured logs + operator_events table is sufficient for MVP observability |\n   405→| Privileged historical entropy submission | Allow a backend-only function to submit a historical slot hash and settle matches that missed the SlotHashes window (~200s). Would enable recovery from extended backend outages without timeout refund. Requires on-chain changes (trusted caller + verified slot hash). |\n   406→\n   407→---\n   408→\n   409→## Validation Plan\n   410→\n   411→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   412→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   413→| 1 | Secret is CSPRNG, commitment matches on-chain algorithm | Unit test: generate secret, compute commitment, verify against Rust `verify_commitment` | Test output |\n   414→| 2 | Partial tx is valid and co-signable | Integration test: build tx, user co-signs, submit to bankrun validator | Tx confirmation |\n   415→| 3 | Settlement worker detects locked matches | Integration test: create + join match in bankrun, verify worker picks it up within poll interval | Worker log + DB state |\n   416→| 4 | Settlement succeeds with correct secret | Integration test: full lifecycle in bankrun — create, join, settle, verify on-chain state | On-chain match PDA in PHASE_SETTLED |\n   417→| 5 | Settlement retries on transient failure | Unit test: mock RPC failure, verify retry with backoff, verify max retries respected | Test output + operator_events |\n   418→| 6 | Rounds endpoint redacts secret pre-settlement | HTTP test: GET round before settlement → no secret; after → secret present | Response body |\n   419→| 7 | Auth rejects invalid/expired signatures | HTTP test: submit with wrong key → 401; submit with old timestamp → 401 | Response status |\n   420→| 8 | Rate limiter enforces per-wallet and global limits | HTTP test: exceed per-wallet limit → 429; exceed global limit → 429 | Response status + Retry-After header |\n   421→| 9 | Health endpoint reports accurate state | HTTP test: check health with DB up/down, check balance reporting | Response body |\n   422→| 10 | Duplicate nonce returns 409 | HTTP test: create with same wallet+nonce twice → first 200, second 409 | Response status |\n   423→\n   424→---\n   425→\n   426→## Completion Signal\n   427→\n   428→### Implementation Checklist\n   429→\n   430→#### Infrastructure\n   431→- [x] [infra] Add PostgreSQL to devcontainer (done: installed via apt in Dockerfile + auto-start in startup.sh + `rng_utopia_dev` database created. `DATABASE_URL=postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n   432→- [x] [infra] Scaffold `services/backend/` package: `package.json` (name `@rng-utopia/backend`), `tsconfig.json`, Hono HTTP server entry point (`src/index.ts`), env config loader (`src/config.ts`) reading `DATABASE_URL`, `RPC_URL`, `SERVER_KEYPAIR`, `PORT`. Verify `pnpm install` and `pnpm build` succeed. Add `dev` script. (done: iteration 1)\n   433→\n   434→#### Database\n   435→- [x] [backend] Postgres migrations: create `rounds` and `operator_events` tables matching the Core Design schema (all columns, types, constraints). Add indexes on `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`. Use a simple migration runner (e.g. `postgres-migrations` or raw SQL files with version tracking). Migrations must be idempotent. (done: iteration 2)\n   436→- [x] [backend] DB client module (`src/db.ts`): connection pool (`pg` or `postgres` library), typed query functions for: `insertRound`, `updateRoundPhase`, `getRoundByPda`, `getRoundsByPhase`, `insertOperatorEvent`. Phase transitions must be unidirectional (application-level guard). `updated_at` set on every phase change. `secret` column never logged. (done: iteration 3)\n   437→\n   438→#### Core Signing Module\n   439→- [x] [backend] Secret generation + commitment utilities (`src/fairness.ts`): generate 32-byte secret via `crypto.randomBytes(32)`, compute commitment using same algorithm as `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` (sha256). PDA derivation matching on-chain seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]`. Export typed functions. Add unit tests inline or in `src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts`. (done: iteration 4)\n   440→- [x] [backend] Partial transaction builder (`src/tx-builder.ts`): build `create_match` instruction using the coinflip IDL (`packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json`), set creator wallet as fee payer, server keypair as `server` signer, pass commitment + tier + side + nonce as args. Partially sign with server keypair. Return base64-serialized transaction + match PDA. Fetch recent blockhash at build time. (done: iteration 5)\n   441→- [x] [backend] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` endpoint handler (`src/routes/create.ts`): validate request body, generate secret, compute commitment, derive PDA, check for duplicate PDA in DB (409 Conflict), build + partial-sign tx, store round in DB (phase `created`), write `secret_generated` operator event, return `{transaction, matchPda, commitment}`. Wire into Hono router. (done: iteration 6)\n   442→\n   443→#### Authentication & Rate Limiting\n   444→- [x] [backend] Request authentication middleware (`src/middleware/auth.ts`): verify Ed25519 signature over canonical payload `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})`. Use `@noble/ed25519` or `tweetnacl`. Reject if timestamp > 60s from server time (configurable via `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS`). Return 401 on invalid/missing signature. Skip for GET routes. (done: iteration 7)\n   445→- [x] [backend] Rate limiting middleware (`src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`): in-memory sliding window, per-wallet limit (default 10/min via `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET`), global limit (default 100/min via `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL`). Return 429 with `Retry-After` header. Apply only to POST routes. Counters reset on service restart (acceptable for MVP). (done: iteration 8)\n   446→\n   447→#### Settlement Worker\n   448→- [x] [backend] Settlement worker poll loop (`src/worker/settlement.ts`): poll chain via `getProgramAccounts` (or `connection.getAccountInfo` for known PDAs) for `CoinflipMatch` accounts in `PHASE_LOCKED` where `server` field matches service keypair. Check `target_slot` reached (current slot >= target_slot). Configurable poll interval (default 2s via `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS`). Start worker on service boot. Log `match_detected` operator event for newly discovered locked matches. (done: iteration 9)\n   449→- [ ] [backend] Settle transaction builder + submission (`src/worker/settle-tx.ts`): retrieve secret from `rounds` table by PDA, build `settle` instruction with all required accounts (match PDA, config PDA, entropy account, treasury, creator, opponent, creator_profile, opponent_profile, platform_program, system_program). Entropy account address configurable via `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` env var (mock for tests, SlotHashes sysvar for production). Submit with server keypair as caller. On success: update DB phase to `settled`, store `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`. Log `settle_submitted` / `settle_confirmed` operator events.\n   450→- [ ] [backend] Settlement retry logic (`src/worker/retry.ts`): on transient failure (tx dropped, blockhash expired, network error), retry up to 5 times with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s). On permanent failure (commitment mismatch, invalid phase, account not found), mark round as failed, log `settle_failed` operator event, do not retry. If `resolve_deadline` passed without settlement, log `timeout_detected` event (on-chain refund is user-triggered, not backend-triggered). Log `settle_retried` on each retry attempt.\n   451→\n   452→#### Read Endpoints & Observability\n   453→- [ ] [backend] `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` endpoint (`src/routes/rounds.ts`): query round by PDA from DB. Return 404 for unknown PDAs. For unsettled rounds: omit `secret` field. For settled rounds: include `secret`, `resultHash`, `resultSide`, `winner`, `settleTx`. Include `verification` object with human-readable check descriptions. Response uses camelCase. No sensitive operational data exposed.\n   454→- [ ] [backend] `GET /health` endpoint (`src/routes/health.ts`) + structured logging (`src/logger.ts`): health returns service version, server pubkey, SOL balance, DB connectivity, worker running status, unsettled count, oldest unsettled age. All log output structured JSON (timestamp, level, message, optional PDA context). SOL balance below threshold (default 0.1 SOL via `MIN_SOL_BALANCE`) triggers warning log. No secrets or private keys in logs at any level.\n   455→\n   456→#### Testing\n   457→- [ ] [test] Unit tests (`src/__tests__/`): secret generation produces 32 bytes, commitment matches `packages/fairness` algorithm, PDA derivation matches on-chain seeds, auth middleware rejects invalid/expired signatures and accepts valid ones, rate limiter enforces per-wallet and global limits and returns correct `Retry-After` header.\n   458→- [ ] [test] Integration tests for full create → join → settle lifecycle against bankrun: create match via POST endpoint → verify DB state → simulate join on-chain (bankrun) → trigger worker poll → verify settlement tx lands → verify DB updated to `settled` → verify GET /rounds/:pda returns secret and verification payload.\n   459→- [ ] [test] HTTP endpoint tests: POST /create with valid auth → 200, invalid signature → 401, expired timestamp → 401, duplicate nonce → 409, rate limit exceeded → 429. GET /rounds/:pda → 200 for known, 404 for unknown. GET /health → 200 with expected fields.\n   460→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   461→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   462→- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   463→\n   464→### Testing Requirements\n   465→\n   466→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   467→\n   468→#### Code Quality\n   469→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   470→- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   471→- [ ] No lint errors\n   472→\n   473→#### Functional Verification\n   474→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   475→- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   476→- [ ] Error states handled\n   477→\n   478→#### Visual Regression\n   479→- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   480→- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   481→- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n   482→- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are in scope\n   483→\n   484→#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   485→- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   486→- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   487→\n   488→#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   489→- [ ] No JS console errors\n   490→- [ ] No failed network requests\n   491→\n   492→#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   493→\n   494→Before declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\n   495→makes sense from a player's perspective. Customize this list per spec.\n   496→\n   497→- [ ] Create request returns valid partial transaction that can be co-signed\n   498→- [ ] Settlement completes automatically after opponent joins (no manual trigger)\n   499→- [ ] Verification endpoint shows correct data for settled rounds\n   500→- [ ] Secret is never exposed for unsettled rounds\n   501→- [ ] Health endpoint reflects actual service state\n   502→- [ ] Rate limiting triggers at configured thresholds\n   503→- [ ] [Add spec-specific checks here]\n   504→\n   505→### Iteration Instructions\n   506→\n   507→If ANY check fails:\n   508→1. Identify the specific issue\n   509→2. Fix the code\n   510→3. Re-run tests\n   511→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   512→5. Check again\n   513→\n   514→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   515→\n   516→### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   517→\n   518→After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   519→`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   520→1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   521→2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   522→3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   523→4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   524→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af244c03-5c35-4a31-9aaa-3171645fdb08","uuid":"ad087ff8-dca3-42f7-9eb6-7ecd804074b4","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/006-fairness-backend/spec.md","content":"# Specification: [006] Fairness Backend — Coinflip MVP\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 9 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nOff-chain service that holds server secrets and orchestrates the commit-reveal fairness\nmodel defined in Spec 005 (Hybrid Fairness). Today the frontend generates secrets\nclient-side (dev-mode) — this service moves secret generation to the server, co-signs\nmatch creation transactions, watches for locked matches, and settles them by revealing\nthe secret on-chain.\n\nScoped to **coinflip only**. Crash, Lord of RNGs, and other games are explicitly deferred\nuntil the coinflip backend is proven stable.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want the server to generate and guard the secret so that neither I nor\n  the server alone can predict the outcome.\n- As a player, I want to create a match with a single wallet approval so that the\n  experience feels instant despite server co-signing.\n- As a player, I want my match settled automatically after my opponent joins so that I\n  don't have to take any action to see the result.\n- As an operator, I want locked matches settled within seconds of entropy availability\n  so that players never wait unnecessarily.\n- As a verifier, I want a public endpoint that serves the secret (post-settlement) and\n  all inputs to the result formula so that I can independently confirm fairness.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Coinflip (Phase 1), Backend Services\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 — required before coinflip can leave dev-mode fairness\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `docs/specs/005-hybrid-fairness/spec.md` — On-chain commit-reveal + slot hash model\n- `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` — Architecture patterns, testing strategy\n- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — VRF provider decision, fee structure\n- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/create_match.rs` — Account layout, signer requirements\n- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/settle.rs` — Permissionless settlement, account layout, event shape\n- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` — `CoinflipMatch` fields, phases, `MatchSettled` event\n- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fairness.rs` — `verify_commitment()`, `derive_result()`, `ALGORITHM_VERSION`\n- `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fees.rs` — 300 bps total, `calculate_net_payout()`\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` — `computeCommitment()`, `verifyCommitment()` (reuse in backend)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` — Typed IDL for tx building\n\n---\n\n## Core Design\n\n### Architecture\n\nSingle Node.js/TypeScript process using **Hono** (lightweight HTTP framework) with three\ninternal modules:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                 Fairness Service             │\n│                                             │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐ │\n│  │ Signing  │  │Settlement│  │  Rounds   │ │\n│  │ Module   │  │ Worker   │  │  Module   │ │\n│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └─────┬─────┘ │\n│       │              │              │       │\n│       └──────────┬───┘──────────────┘       │\n│                  │                          │\n│           ┌──────┴──────┐                   │\n│           │  Postgres   │                   │\n│           │  (rounds +  │                   │\n│           │   events)   │                   │\n│           └─────────────┘                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Signing Module** — Handles `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`. Generates secret,\ncomputes commitment, builds the `create_match` transaction using the coinflip IDL,\npartially signs with the server keypair, returns the serialized transaction to the caller.\n\n**Settlement Worker** — Polls for matches in PHASE_LOCKED where `target_slot` has been\nreached. Reads entropy, builds and submits the `settle` transaction with the stored secret.\nRetries on transient failures; logs to `operator_events`.\n\n**Rounds Module** — Handles `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`. Serves round lifecycle data\nand verification payloads. Reads from DB, redacts secret for unsettled rounds.\n\n### Signer Model\n\nOne server keypair for MVP, loaded from environment (`SERVER_KEYPAIR`). This keypair:\n- Co-signs `create_match` transactions (appears as `server: Signer` in the instruction)\n- Pays the settlement transaction fee (~0.000005 SOL per settle)\n- Does NOT need to be the same key that calls `settle` (settle is permissionless — anyone\n  with the secret can call it), but using the server key simplifies operational monitoring\n\nFuture: split into separate signing authority (cold, for create) and settlement authority\n(hot, for settle). The on-chain program already supports this — `settle` has no server\nsigner constraint.\n\n### Transaction Flow\n\n```\nPlayer                    Backend                     Chain\n  │                          │                          │\n  ├─ POST /create ──────────►│                          │\n  │  {tier, side, wallet}    │                          │\n  │                          │─ generate secret         │\n  │                          │─ commitment = sha256()   │\n  │                          │─ build create_match tx   │\n  │                          │─ server partial-sign     │\n  │                          │─ store secret in DB      │\n  │◄─ {tx, matchPda} ───────│                          │\n  │                          │                          │\n  ├─ co-sign + submit ─────────────────────────────────►│\n  │                          │                          │─ create match PDA\n  │                          │                          │\n  │         ... opponent joins (user-submitted) ...     │\n  │                          │                          │─ PHASE_LOCKED, target_slot set\n  │                          │                          │\n  │                          │◄── poll / subscription ──│\n  │                          │─ wait for target_slot    │\n  │                          │─ build settle tx         │\n  │                          │─ submit settle ─────────►│\n  │                          │                          │─ verify commitment\n  │                          │                          │─ derive result\n  │                          │                          │─ pay winner\n  │                          │                          │─ emit MatchSettled\n  │                          │                          │\n  │                          │─ update DB (settled)     │\n```\n\n### Database Schema\n\nTwo tables — `rounds` for state, `operator_events` for append-only audit trail.\n\n#### `rounds`\n\n| Column | Type | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| `pda` | `TEXT PRIMARY KEY` | Base58 match PDA address |\n| `game` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `'coinflip'` (extensible later) |\n| `creator` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 creator wallet |\n| `server_key` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 server pubkey used |\n| `secret` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | 32-byte server secret |\n| `commitment` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | SHA256(secret) |\n| `tier` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Tier index |\n| `side` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Creator's chosen side |\n| `nonce` | `BIGINT NOT NULL` | Match nonce |\n| `phase` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `created`, `locked`, `settling`, `settled`, `expired` |\n| `target_slot` | `BIGINT` | Set when match transitions to locked |\n| `settle_tx` | `TEXT` | Settlement tx signature |\n| `settle_attempts` | `INT DEFAULT 0` | Retry counter |\n| `result_hash` | `BYTEA` | 32-byte result (post-settlement) |\n| `result_side` | `SMALLINT` | 0=Heads, 1=Tails (post-settlement) |\n| `winner` | `TEXT` | Base58 winner address (post-settlement) |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n\n#### `operator_events`\n\n| Column | Type | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY` | Auto-increment |\n| `pda` | `TEXT` | Nullable — some events are system-level |\n| `event_type` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `secret_generated`, `tx_built`, `match_detected`, `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, `settle_retried`, `timeout_detected` |\n| `payload` | `JSONB` | Event-specific data |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n\n**Indexes**: `rounds(phase)` for settlement worker queries, `rounds(creator)` for lookup,\n`operator_events(pda, created_at)` for round history, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)` for monitoring.\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n<!-- FR acceptance criteria checkboxes are audited by /gap-analysis after completion.\n     Each checkbox gets an HTML comment annotation: satisfied/deferred/gap with evidence. -->\n\n### FR-1: Secret Generation & Transaction Signing\n\nThe service generates a cryptographically secure secret, computes the commitment,\nbuilds a `create_match` transaction with the server's partial signature, and returns it\nto the requesting wallet for co-signing and submission.\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`\n\n**Request body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"wallet\": \"<base58 creator pubkey>\",\n  \"tier\": 3,\n  \"side\": 0,\n  \"nonce\": 42,\n  \"timestamp\": 1710000000,\n  \"signature\": \"<base58 Ed25519 signature over canonical payload>\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response** (200):\n```json\n{\n  \"transaction\": \"<base64 serialized partial tx>\",\n  \"matchPda\": \"<base58 PDA address>\",\n  \"commitment\": \"<hex commitment>\"\n}\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Secret is 32 bytes generated via Node.js `crypto.randomBytes(32)` (CSPRNG)\n- [ ] Commitment is computed using the same algorithm as `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` (`sha256(secret)`)\n- [ ] Transaction is built using the coinflip IDL (`create_match` instruction) with correct accounts and args\n- [ ] Server keypair partially signs the transaction (server appears as `server: Signer`)\n- [ ] User's wallet is set as fee payer — server pays zero on-chain cost for creation\n- [ ] Secret is stored in the `rounds` table keyed by match PDA before the response is returned\n- [ ] An `operator_events` entry of type `secret_generated` is written\n- [ ] Match PDA is derived using seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]` matching the on-chain program\n- [ ] If the same PDA already exists in the DB (duplicate nonce), the endpoint returns 409 Conflict\n- [ ] Recent blockhash is fetched at request time (transaction expires naturally via Solana's ~60s blockhash window)\n\n### FR-2: Settlement Worker\n\nA background process that detects locked matches and submits settlement transactions\nonce entropy is available.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Worker polls the chain (via `getProgramAccounts` or equivalent) for `CoinflipMatch` accounts in `PHASE_LOCKED` where the `server` field matches the service's keypair\n- [ ] For each locked match, worker checks if `target_slot` has been reached (current slot >= target_slot)\n- [ ] Worker retrieves the stored secret from the `rounds` table using the match PDA\n- [ ] Worker builds and submits the `settle` instruction with the secret, all required accounts (match PDA, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, profiles, platform program), and the server keypair as caller\n- [ ] On successful settlement, worker updates the round's DB phase to `settled` and stores `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`\n- [ ] On transient failure (tx dropped, blockhash expired, network error), worker retries up to 5 times with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s)\n- [ ] On permanent failure (commitment mismatch, invalid phase, account not found), worker marks the round as failed and logs to `operator_events` without retrying\n- [ ] Worker poll interval is configurable (default: 2 seconds)\n- [ ] Worker logs each attempt to `operator_events` with type `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, or `settle_retried`\n- [ ] If `resolve_deadline` has passed and settlement has not succeeded, worker logs a `timeout_detected` event (the on-chain timeout refund is triggered by any user, not by the backend)\n\n### FR-3: Round State Storage\n\nPostgres tables store the full lifecycle of each round with an append-only operator\nevent log for auditability.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `rounds` table schema matches the design in Core Design section (all columns, types, constraints)\n- [ ] `operator_events` table schema matches the design in Core Design section\n- [ ] Phase transitions follow this state machine: `created` → `locked` → `settling` → `settled`; or `created` → `expired` (if tx never lands on-chain). The worker discovers matches on-chain via polling — no intermediate states needed for phases the backend can't directly observe.\n- [ ] Phase transitions are unidirectional — no backward transitions allowed at the application layer\n- [ ] `secret` column is stored as raw bytes, never logged or exposed in error messages\n- [ ] `updated_at` is set on every phase transition\n- [ ] Database migrations are versioned and idempotent (can re-run safely)\n- [ ] Indexes exist on `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, and `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n\n### FR-4: Round Verification Endpoint\n\nPublic endpoint serving round lifecycle data and post-settlement verification payloads.\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`\n\n**Response** (settled round):\n```json\n{\n  \"pda\": \"<base58>\",\n  \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n  \"phase\": \"settled\",\n  \"commitment\": \"<hex>\",\n  \"secret\": \"<hex>\",\n  \"algorithmVersion\": 1,\n  \"targetSlot\": 312000000,\n  \"resultHash\": \"<hex>\",\n  \"resultSide\": 0,\n  \"winner\": \"<base58>\",\n  \"settleTx\": \"<base58 tx signature>\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-11T12:00:00Z\",\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"commitmentCheck\": \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n    \"resultFormula\": \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n    \"entropySource\": \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Endpoint returns round data for any known PDA\n- [ ] For unsettled rounds (`phase` != `settled`), the `secret` field is omitted from the response\n- [ ] For settled rounds, the response includes `secret`, `resultHash`, `resultSide`, `winner`, and `settleTx`\n- [ ] Response includes a `verification` object with human-readable descriptions of the fairness checks\n- [ ] Endpoint returns 404 for unknown PDAs\n- [ ] Response is JSON with consistent field naming (camelCase)\n- [ ] No sensitive operational data (server keypair, internal IDs) is exposed\n\n### FR-5: Request Authentication\n\nRequests to state-changing endpoints are authenticated via wallet-signed payloads\nto prevent spoofing without requiring session infrastructure.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` requires a valid Ed25519 signature over a canonical payload\n- [ ] Canonical payload is: `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})` with keys in that exact order\n- [ ] Signature is verified against the `wallet` pubkey using `@noble/ed25519` or `tweetnacl`\n- [ ] Requests with a `timestamp` more than 60 seconds from server time are rejected (replay protection)\n- [ ] Requests with an invalid or missing signature return 401 Unauthorized\n- [ ] `GET` endpoints (rounds, health) require no authentication\n- [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable (default: 60 seconds)\n\n### FR-6: Health & Observability\n\nOperational endpoints and structured logging for monitoring service health.\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n\n**Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"serverKey\": \"<base58 server pubkey>\",\n  \"solBalance\": 1.5,\n  \"dbConnected\": true,\n  \"workerRunning\": true,\n  \"unsettledCount\": 3,\n  \"oldestUnsettledAge\": 12\n}\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns server status including: service version, server public key, SOL balance of server keypair, DB connectivity, worker status, count of unsettled rounds, age (seconds) of oldest unsettled round\n- [ ] Health endpoint requires no authentication\n- [ ] All log output is structured JSON (timestamp, level, message, optional fields)\n- [ ] Logs include round PDA context where applicable (settlement attempts, errors)\n- [ ] No secrets or private keys appear in logs at any level\n- [ ] SOL balance below a configurable threshold (default: 0.1 SOL) triggers a warning-level log on each health check\n- [ ] `operator_events` table is queryable for monitoring dashboards (no dedicated endpoint required for MVP; direct DB access is acceptable)\n\n### FR-7: Rate Limiting\n\nPer-wallet and global rate limits to prevent abuse of the create endpoint.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` is rate-limited per wallet (default: 10 requests per minute)\n- [ ] A global rate limit caps total create requests (default: 100 requests per minute)\n- [ ] Rate limiting is in-memory (no Redis dependency for MVP)\n- [ ] Exceeded limits return HTTP 429 with a `Retry-After` header\n- [ ] `GET` endpoints are not rate-limited for MVP\n- [ ] Rate limit windows and thresholds are configurable via environment variables\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Server generates secrets and co-signs create transactions — frontend no longer holds secrets\n- Locked matches are settled automatically within 10 seconds of entropy availability (p95)\n- Settlement retry logic handles transient RPC failures without manual intervention\n- Any settled round can be independently verified via the public rounds endpoint\n- Service runs as a single process with < 100 MB memory footprint under normal load\n- Zero SOL cost for match creation (server is signer but user is fee payer)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Spec 005 (Hybrid Fairness) — on-chain commit-reveal model must be implemented. **Spec 005 must set timeout to 300s** (not 120s) so that if the backend is down, players get a permissionless refund. The backend requires server co-sign for new games, so no new matches can be created during downtime anyway — timeout refund is the complete safety net.\n- Coinflip program deployed with `server: Signer` on `create_match` and permissionless `settle`\n- `packages/fairness/` — `computeCommitment()` and `verifyCommitment()` functions\n- `packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` — Typed IDL for transaction building\n- Postgres instance (local Docker for dev, managed for production)\n- Solana RPC endpoint with `getProgramAccounts` support\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- The on-chain coinflip program is already deployed with the Spec 005 commit-reveal model\n- A single server keypair is sufficient for MVP (no key rotation during operation)\n- In-memory rate limiting is acceptable (service restarts reset counters)\n- Postgres is the only external dependency (no Redis, no message queue)\n- The settlement worker is the only settler — no competing settlers for MVP\n- Frontend will be updated separately to call the backend instead of generating secrets client-side\n\n---\n\n## Deferred Items\n\n| Item | Rationale |\n|------|-----------|\n| Multi-game support (Crash, Lord of RNGs, Slots) | Prove the model on coinflip first; each game has different entropy capture timing |\n| Key rotation / split authorities | Single keypair is fine for MVP; add when operational maturity requires it |\n| WebSocket push for settlement notifications | Frontend already polls on-chain state; adding WS is a UX optimization, not a blocker |\n| Redis-backed rate limiting | In-memory is sufficient until horizontal scaling is needed |\n| Batch settlement (multiple matches per tx) | Premature optimization; single-match settlement is simpler to debug |\n| Verification page / UI | The endpoint exists; a standalone verification UI is a frontend concern |\n| Automated server keypair funding | Manual top-up for MVP; automate when tx volume justifies it |\n| Horizontal scaling / multiple workers | Single process handles expected MVP load; scale when needed |\n| Event-driven settlement (geyser/websocket subscription) | Polling is simpler and sufficient; switch if latency budget tightens |\n| Metrics endpoint (Prometheus) | Structured logs + operator_events table is sufficient for MVP observability |\n| Privileged historical entropy submission | Allow a backend-only function to submit a historical slot hash and settle matches that missed the SlotHashes window (~200s). Would enable recovery from extended backend outages without timeout refund. Requires on-chain changes (trusted caller + verified slot hash). |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Secret is CSPRNG, commitment matches on-chain algorithm | Unit test: generate secret, compute commitment, verify against Rust `verify_commitment` | Test output |\n| 2 | Partial tx is valid and co-signable | Integration test: build tx, user co-signs, submit to bankrun validator | Tx confirmation |\n| 3 | Settlement worker detects locked matches | Integration test: create + join match in bankrun, verify worker picks it up within poll interval | Worker log + DB state |\n| 4 | Settlement succeeds with correct secret | Integration test: full lifecycle in bankrun — create, join, settle, verify on-chain state | On-chain match PDA in PHASE_SETTLED |\n| 5 | Settlement retries on transient failure | Unit test: mock RPC failure, verify retry with backoff, verify max retries respected | Test output + operator_events |\n| 6 | Rounds endpoint redacts secret pre-settlement | HTTP test: GET round before settlement → no secret; after → secret present | Response body |\n| 7 | Auth rejects invalid/expired signatures | HTTP test: submit with wrong key → 401; submit with old timestamp → 401 | Response status |\n| 8 | Rate limiter enforces per-wallet and global limits | HTTP test: exceed per-wallet limit → 429; exceed global limit → 429 | Response status + Retry-After header |\n| 9 | Health endpoint reports accurate state | HTTP test: check health with DB up/down, check balance reporting | Response body |\n| 10 | Duplicate nonce returns 409 | HTTP test: create with same wallet+nonce twice → first 200, second 409 | Response status |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Infrastructure\n- [x] [infra] Add PostgreSQL to devcontainer (done: installed via apt in Dockerfile + auto-start in startup.sh + `rng_utopia_dev` database created. `DATABASE_URL=postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n- [x] [infra] Scaffold `services/backend/` package: `package.json` (name `@rng-utopia/backend`), `tsconfig.json`, Hono HTTP server entry point (`src/index.ts`), env config loader (`src/config.ts`) reading `DATABASE_URL`, `RPC_URL`, `SERVER_KEYPAIR`, `PORT`. Verify `pnpm install` and `pnpm build` succeed. Add `dev` script. (done: iteration 1)\n\n#### Database\n- [x] [backend] Postgres migrations: create `rounds` and `operator_events` tables matching the Core Design schema (all columns, types, constraints). Add indexes on `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`. Use a simple migration runner (e.g. `postgres-migrations` or raw SQL files with version tracking). Migrations must be idempotent. (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [backend] DB client module (`src/db.ts`): connection pool (`pg` or `postgres` library), typed query functions for: `insertRound`, `updateRoundPhase`, `getRoundByPda`, `getRoundsByPhase`, `insertOperatorEvent`. Phase transitions must be unidirectional (application-level guard). `updated_at` set on every phase change. `secret` column never logged. (done: iteration 3)\n\n#### Core Signing Module\n- [x] [backend] Secret generation + commitment utilities (`src/fairness.ts`): generate 32-byte secret via `crypto.randomBytes(32)`, compute commitment using same algorithm as `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` (sha256). PDA derivation matching on-chain seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]`. Export typed functions. Add unit tests inline or in `src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts`. (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [backend] Partial transaction builder (`src/tx-builder.ts`): build `create_match` instruction using the coinflip IDL (`packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json`), set creator wallet as fee payer, server keypair as `server` signer, pass commitment + tier + side + nonce as args. Partially sign with server keypair. Return base64-serialized transaction + match PDA. Fetch recent blockhash at build time. (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [backend] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` endpoint handler (`src/routes/create.ts`): validate request body, generate secret, compute commitment, derive PDA, check for duplicate PDA in DB (409 Conflict), build + partial-sign tx, store round in DB (phase `created`), write `secret_generated` operator event, return `{transaction, matchPda, commitment}`. Wire into Hono router. (done: iteration 6)\n\n#### Authentication & Rate Limiting\n- [x] [backend] Request authentication middleware (`src/middleware/auth.ts`): verify Ed25519 signature over canonical payload `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})`. Use `@noble/ed25519` or `tweetnacl`. Reject if timestamp > 60s from server time (configurable via `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS`). Return 401 on invalid/missing signature. Skip for GET routes. (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [backend] Rate limiting middleware (`src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`): in-memory sliding window, per-wallet limit (default 10/min via `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET`), global limit (default 100/min via `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL`). Return 429 with `Retry-After` header. Apply only to POST routes. Counters reset on service restart (acceptable for MVP). (done: iteration 8)\n\n#### Settlement Worker\n- [x] [backend] Settlement worker poll loop (`src/worker/settlement.ts`): poll chain via `getProgramAccounts` (or `connection.getAccountInfo` for known PDAs) for `CoinflipMatch` accounts in `PHASE_LOCKED` where `server` field matches service keypair. Check `target_slot` reached (current slot >= target_slot). Configurable poll interval (default 2s via `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS`). Start worker on service boot. Log `match_detected` operator event for newly discovered locked matches. (done: iteration 9)\n- [ ] [backend] Settle transaction builder + submission (`src/worker/settle-tx.ts`): retrieve secret from `rounds` table by PDA, build `settle` instruction with all required accounts (match PDA, config PDA, entropy account, treasury, creator, opponent, creator_profile, opponent_profile, platform_program, system_program). Entropy account address configurable via `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` env var (mock for tests, SlotHashes sysvar for production). Submit with server keypair as caller. On success: update DB phase to `settled`, store `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`. Log `settle_submitted` / `settle_confirmed` operator events.\n- [ ] [backend] Settlement retry logic (`src/worker/retry.ts`): on transient failure (tx dropped, blockhash expired, network error), retry up to 5 times with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s). On permanent failure (commitment mismatch, invalid phase, account not found), mark round as failed, log `settle_failed` operator event, do not retry. If `resolve_deadline` passed without settlement, log `timeout_detected` event (on-chain refund is user-triggered, not backend-triggered). Log `settle_retried` on each retry attempt.\n\n#### Read Endpoints & Observability\n- [ ] [backend] `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` endpoint (`src/routes/rounds.ts`): query round by PDA from DB. Return 404 for unknown PDAs. For unsettled rounds: omit `secret` field. For settled rounds: include `secret`, `resultHash`, `resultSide`, `winner`, `settleTx`. Include `verification` object with human-readable check descriptions. Response uses camelCase. No sensitive operational data exposed.\n- [ ] [backend] `GET /health` endpoint (`src/routes/health.ts`) + structured logging (`src/logger.ts`): health returns service version, server pubkey, SOL balance, DB connectivity, worker running status, unsettled count, oldest unsettled age. All log output structured JSON (timestamp, level, message, optional PDA context). SOL balance below threshold (default 0.1 SOL via `MIN_SOL_BALANCE`) triggers warning log. No secrets or private keys in logs at any level.\n\n#### Testing\n- [ ] [test] Unit tests (`src/__tests__/`): secret generation produces 32 bytes, commitment matches `packages/fairness` algorithm, PDA derivation matches on-chain seeds, auth middleware rejects invalid/expired signatures and accepts valid ones, rate limiter enforces per-wallet and global limits and returns correct `Retry-After` header.\n- [ ] [test] Integration tests for full create → join → settle lifecycle against bankrun: create match via POST endpoint → verify DB state → simulate join on-chain (bankrun) → trigger worker poll → verify settlement tx lands → verify DB updated to `settled` → verify GET /rounds/:pda returns secret and verification payload.\n- [ ] [test] HTTP endpoint tests: POST /create with valid auth → 200, invalid signature → 401, expired timestamp → 401, duplicate nonce → 409, rate limit exceeded → 429. GET /rounds/:pda → 200 for known, 404 for unknown. GET /health → 200 with expected fields.\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are in scope\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\nBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\nmakes sense from a player's perspective. Customize this list per spec.\n\n- [ ] Create request returns valid partial transaction that can be co-signed\n- [ ] Settlement completes automatically after opponent joins (no manual trigger)\n- [ ] Verification endpoint shows correct data for settled rounds\n- [ ] Secret is never exposed for unsettled rounds\n- [ ] Health endpoint reflects actual service state\n- [ ] Rate limiting triggers at configured thresholds\n- [ ] [Add spec-specific checks here]\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":524,"startLine":1,"totalLines":524}}}
