{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011HhARMuZiEv2CvrvnTiMWR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { randomBytes, createHash } from \"node:crypto\";\n     2→import { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     3→\n     4→export const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n     5→  \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\",\n     6→);\n     7→\n     8→/** Generate a 32-byte cryptographically secure random secret. */\n     9→export function generateSecret(): Buffer {\n    10→  return randomBytes(32);\n    11→}\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Compute commitment = sha256(secret).\n    15→ * Matches the algorithm in packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts.\n    16→ */\n    17→export function computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n    18→  return createHash(\"sha256\").update(secret).digest();\n    19→}\n    20→\n    21→/**\n    22→ * Derive match PDA using seeds [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()].\n    23→ * Matches the on-chain program's PDA derivation.\n    24→ */\n    25→export function deriveMatchPda(\n    26→  creator: PublicKey,\n    27→  nonce: number | bigint,\n    28→): [PublicKey, number] {\n    29→  const nonceBuf = Buffer.alloc(8);\n    30→  nonceBuf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(nonce));\n    31→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    32→    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), nonceBuf],\n    33→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n    34→  );\n    35→}\n    36→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af244c03-5c35-4a31-9aaa-3171645fdb08","uuid":"3543d700-b5e2-4cc0-934e-1b03e58dc8e9","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/fairness.ts","content":"import { randomBytes, createHash } from \"node:crypto\";\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\",\n);\n\n/** Generate a 32-byte cryptographically secure random secret. */\nexport function generateSecret(): Buffer {\n  return randomBytes(32);\n}\n\n/**\n * Compute commitment = sha256(secret).\n * Matches the algorithm in packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts.\n */\nexport function computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return createHash(\"sha256\").update(secret).digest();\n}\n\n/**\n * Derive match PDA using seeds [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()].\n * Matches the on-chain program's PDA derivation.\n */\nexport function deriveMatchPda(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  nonce: number | bigint,\n): [PublicKey, number] {\n  const nonceBuf = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  nonceBuf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(nonce));\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), nonceBuf],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n","numLines":36,"startLine":1,"totalLines":36}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QesQJiLaruKmeL783EMFV4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me also quickly check the coinflip state layout to understand the account data parsing needed for building the settle transaction. I need to understand what fields I can read from the CoinflipMatch account data.\n\nFrom the Explore agent:\n- CoinflipMatch account layout (total 246 bytes = 8 disc + 238 InitSpace):\n  - [0..8]: Anchor discriminator\n  - [8..40]: creator (Pubkey, 32 bytes)\n  - [40..72]: opponent (Pubkey, 32 bytes)\n  - [72..104]: server (Pubkey, 32 bytes)\n  - [104]: tier (u8, 1 byte)\n  - [105..113]: entry_amount (u64, 8 bytes)\n  - [113]: creator_side (u8, 1 byte)\n  - [114]: phase (u8, 1 byte)\n  - [115..147]: commitment ([u8; 32], 32 bytes)\n  - [147]: algorithm_ver (u8, 1 byte)\n  - [148..156]: target_slot (u64, 8 bytes)\n  - [156..164]: resolve_deadline (i64, 8 bytes)\n\nContinuing through the rest of the struct: result_hash takes up 32 bytes, followed by a single byte for result, then the winner pubkey at 32 bytes, created_at timestamp at 8 bytes, nonce at 8 bytes, bump at 1 byte, and creator_wants_refund as a boolean. But wait, that's already 247 bytes total with the discriminator, which doesn't match the InitSpace of 246 I calculated earlier. Let me recount the actual layout to see where the discrepancy is. I'm getting 240 bytes total for the match account structure, not 238 like the agent mentioned, but the settlement worker already has the correct offsets so I'll move forward. For the settle-tx module, I need to read the creator and opponent from the match PDA, then derive the necessary PDAs including the config account and both player profiles from the platform program.\n\nBuilding the settle instruction requires the discriminator and secret argument, along with eleven accounts in a specific order: the caller, match account, config, 